Its a Shinto blade not Koto. If I do put the hi on it will not be for 
whistling purposes. What makes people think that I would shallowly ruin 
an old blade. I see no reason why the blade cannot be used for Iaido and 
adding a hi on it does not ruin the blade, if done by a proper smith in 
Japan. The blade can still be appreciated. We are obviously looking at 
this from opposite ends. If done correctly and I presented you with the 
blade for the first time you would probably not know that it was modified.
Enore

